import numpy as np
import cv2
from skimage import io
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import matplotlib
In [2]:
def url_to_image(url):
  print("downloading %s" % (url))
  return io.imread(url)

def path_to_image(im_path):
  return cv2.cvtColor(cv2.imread(im_path), cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

matplotlib.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (30.0, 20.0)
In [3]:
img = path_to_image('./obj1.jpg')
img2_origin = img.copy()
img = cv2.resize(img, (0,0), fx=0.5, fy=0.5) 
mask = np.zeros(img.shape[:2],np.uint8)
bgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
fgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
rect = (25,10,200,130)
cv2.grabCut(img,mask,rect,bgdModel,fgdModel,5,cv2.GC_INIT_WITH_RECT)
mask2 = np.where((mask==2)|(mask==0),0,1).astype('uint8')
img = img*mask2[:,:,np.newaxis]
fig = plt.figure()
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
imgplot = plt.imshow(img2_origin)
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
imgplot = plt.imshow(mask2*255, 'gray')
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
imgplot = plt.imshow(img)

img = img = path_to_image('./obj3.jpg')
img = cv2.resize(img, (0,0), fx=0.5, fy=0.5) 

img3_origin=img.copy()

(w,h) = img.shape[:2]
mask = np.zeros( (w,h),np.uint8)
bgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
fgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
rect = (25,25,w-50,h)
cv2.grabCut(img,mask,rect,bgdModel,fgdModel,2,cv2.GC_INIT_WITH_RECT)
mask2 = np.where((mask==2)|(mask==0),0,1).astype('uint8')
img = img*mask2[:,:,np.newaxis]

fig = plt.figure()
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
imgplot = plt.imshow(img3_origin)
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
imgplot = plt.imshow(mask2*255, 'gray')
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
imgplot = plt.imshow(img)

url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mdavydov/ComputerVisionCourse/master/images/pear.jpg"
img = url_to_image(url)
img = cv2.resize(img, (0,0), fx=0.5, fy=0.5) 

img1_origin=img.copy()

(w,h) = img.shape[:2]
print(img.shape[:2])
mask = np.zeros( (w,h),np.uint8)
bgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
fgdModel = np.zeros((1,65),np.float64)
rect = (25,25,w-50,h-50)
cv2.grabCut(img,mask,rect,bgdModel,fgdModel,2,cv2.GC_INIT_WITH_RECT)
mask2 = np.where((mask==2)|(mask==0),0,1).astype('uint8')
img = img*mask2[:,:,np.newaxis]

fig = plt.figure()
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
imgplot = plt.imshow(img1_origin)
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
imgplot = plt.imshow(mask2*255, 'gray')
a = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
imgplot = plt.imshow(img)
